<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Meets Business Tycoons Amid Economic Woes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin met
ten tycoons in the Kremlin Tuesday to discuss settlement of the
recent turmoil on Russia's financial market.
</P>
<P>
The ten business leaders showed their support for the Russian
government at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that Russia's situation is difficult but that
Russia "has a highly skilled government which is taking the
necessary measures," the president's spokesman, Sergei
Yastrzhembsky, told a briefing after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Russia's stock market sharply tumbled last week primarily due
to investors' concerns over the young Russian cabinet's ability to
handle the economic problems under the impact of the Asian
economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
The main stock index has plunged 44 percent since the beginning
of May and the government has tripled interest rates to as high as
150 percent to attract investment.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, they also discussed changes to the tax
system, measures to solve nonpayment problems and proposals on
tariffs for electricity, gas and railroad transportation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
