<HEADLINE> UNDP Supports Bhutan's Local Development Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) and the U.N. Capital Development Fund
have launched a 1.6 million U.S. dollar decentralization effort in
Bhutan, the UNDP said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The project is to strengthen development planning and
administrative authority at district levels.
</P>
<P>
A U.N. official said experiences throughout Africa and
Southeast Asia have shown that decentralization and local planning
are prerequisites for sustainable rural development.
</P>
<P>
Bhutan is a Himalayan kingdom with an area of 46,000 square
kilometers and a population of 600,000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
