<HEADLINE> UNDP in Russia for AIDS Awareness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Fund (UNDP) and the city of Nizhini Movgorod, Russia,
recently organized a benefit concert to raise awareness of the
high risk HIV/AIDS posing to the city's young people, according to
UNDP here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
As of March the number of registered HIV/AIDS cases in this
city of 1.3 million inhabitants was 7,900, but over half the new
infections are believed to have occurred in 1997.
</P>
<P>
U.N. data show that Eastern Europe including Russia threatens
to become one of the next epicenters of HIV/AIDS infection.
</P>
<P>
The concert is one of several planned by UNDP in cities across
Russia to raise awareness of the dangers of the disease and
educate youngsters on how to avoid infection, said UNDP in its
latest publication UNDPflash.  
</P>
</TEXT>
