<HEADLINE> UNDP in Mexico for Ozone Layer Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) provided 2.7 million U.S. dollars to
Mexico last week to help phase out use of ozone depleting
substances in refrigerants' production, UNDP said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Some 87 Mexican enterprises are receiving UNDP assistance,
totaling 15.7 million dollars so far under the Montreal Protocol
Multilateral Fund.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP program in Mexico for ozone protection is its largest in
Latin America.  
</P>
