<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Price Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Oil price of the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) went up by 0.26 U.S. dollars
a barrel last week, the OPEC secretariat said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The average price of OPEC's basket of seven crudes rose to 13.09
dollars a barrel last week from the 12.83 dollars a barrel the
week before.
</P>
<P>
The annual average price stands at 13.20 dollars per barrel,
far less than last year's 18.68 dollars and the benchmark price of
21 dollars per barrel set by OPEC.
</P>
<P>
The organization uses the average price of OPEC's basket of
seven crudes to monitor the change of oil prices worldwide.
</P>
</TEXT>
