<HEADLINE> Peres: Labor Should Provide Netanyahu a </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Peres, also a Knesset (parliament) member, made the remark
while commenting on the ongoing political debate in Israel whether
the Labor Party should support Netanyahu in a parliamentary vote
on Israel's troop redeployment in the West Bank and provide a
political safety net to him if the vote is turned into a motion of
no-confidence.
</P>
<P>
Troop redeployment is crucial to the peace process and Labor
should provide a political safety net to Netanyahu in Knesset
because Labor's policy is to have peace with the Palestinians and
all other Arab nations, Peres said.
</P>
<P>
Ruling coalition whip Meir Sheetrit from Likud called on the
Labor on Monday to support Netanyahu on the second troop
redeployment and provide a political safety net in parliament if
the redeployment issue goes to the Knesset.
</P>
<P>
Senior Labor Knesset members met on Monday and discussed this
request, but decided not to take any position right now.
</P>
<P>
Sheetrit said he will call on Netanyahu to bring the second
troop redeployment up for a vote in the Knesset without worrying
about the threat by Knesset members on the far right to vote
against it.
</P>
<P>
But the coalition National Religious Party (NRP) has urged
Netanyahu to ignore Sheetrit's call for a safety net, saying a
safety net won't help a prime minister who loses the trust of
senior members of his coalition.
</P>
<P>
NRP opposes the government to hand any more West Bank
land over to the Palestinians. 
</P>
