<HEADLINE> Explosion in Tehran Kills 2, Injures 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The explosion at the Islamic
revolutionary court in northern Tehran on Tuesday killed two people
and injured two others, Tehran radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place in the waiting hall at the entrance
of the court, inflicting serious damages to the hall and window
panes nearby, the report said, adding that investigation was
underway on the cause of the explosion.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official news agency IRNA earlier quoted an
official from the court public relations office as saying that
the incident took place at 1:45 p.m. local time (0915 GMT) when
explosives related to a case under investigation were being
carried to the court.
</P>
<P>
The blast happened due to negligence during the transfer of
the explosives, the official said, giving no further details about
the incident. 
</P>
