<HEADLINE> Greece, U.S. Conduct Joint Military Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Greece and the United States Tuesday
began a two-day joint military exercises as part of their efforts
to strengthen the military ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The exercises, codenamed "Alexander the Great'98", is being
conducted in the Greek area of the Pagasitikos gulf, Skiros and
the northeast Aegean Sea, according to the semi-official Athens
News Agency (ANA).
</P>
<P>
The Greek forces participating in the war games include the
32nd marine brigade, three groups of parachutists, two groups of
special forces, Huey and Apache helicopters, a destroyer, five
tank landing craft, two transport carriers, a gunboat and 10-15
Hellenic Air Force aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. forces include the amphibious operations battalion
phibron 6, three landing craft and frogmen, men of the 26th
batallion, two KC-130 and two AC-130 aircraft.
</P>
<P>
During Tuesday's exercises, the Greek and U.S. forces made a
commando assault on the Aegean island of Agios Efstratios.
</P>
