<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa
said Tuesday the upcoming summit of the Organization of the
African Unity will seek ways to settle disputes through peaceful
means and maintain peace on the continent.
</P>
<P>
Moussa, who will lead Egypt's delegation to a ministerial
meeting and the summit held in Burkina Faso on June 4-10, told
reporters that political and security problems in Africa will top
the agenda of the summit.
</P>
<P>
Despite the problems in Africa's political, economic and social
situations, Moussa said, the continent still boasts successes as
"a general economic growth indicates progress."
</P>
<P>
