Belfast on Tuesday the Northern Ireland police force -- the Royal
Ulster Constabulary (RUC) -- will not be disbanded.
</P>
<P>
"There will be no paramilitaries running the police service.
That would be quite wrong," Blair told reporters after meeting
with Ulster Unionist leader David Trimble.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister flew into Belfast from Dublin earlier
Tuesday in his latest drive to bring peace to Northern Ireland. It
is his fourth visit to the troubled province in five weeks.
</P>
<P>
