policing takes place to one of peace and stability and progress,
then hopefully we can get policing done in a normal way which is
what all the members of the RUC want, quite apart from the
public."
</P>
<P>
Blair remains under pressure from unionists over the exact
nature of other controversial parts of the peace agreement,
including the early release of paramilitary prisoners and
decommissioning of arms.
</P>
<P>
Ulster Unionists want to see a start to decommissioning before
they will agree to which parties can take office in the Northern
Ireland Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Blair explained it was for the independent decommissioning body
to decide the precise timing of its work.
</P>
<P>
"There is a process which is already under way and it is for
the independent commission to actually launch their schemes," he
said.  
