<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 24 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market Wednesday closed at 3597.98 as against
Tuesday's close of 3573.21, showing a gain of 24.77 points.
</P>
<P>
The national index edged up by 3.90 points to 1598.38 from
previous close of 1594.48.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar index were, however, quoted
slightly down at 365.10 and 145.42 compared with previous close of
365.22 and 145.47 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities recovered initial sharp losses and even posted
handsome to moderate gains pushing the sensitive index up by over
24 points on stock market Wednesday in the wake of aggressive
purchases by financial institutions coupled with fresh buying by
speculators. 
</P>
