<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australia Imposes No Economic Sanctions Against Pak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Australia has not imposed
economic sanctions against Pakistan in response to its nuclear
tests last week, said a statement of the Australian High
Commission here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian government has moved to implement a range of
measures -- similar to those imposed on India -- to demonstrate
Australia's condemnation of the nuclear tests, and "our desire to
contribute to international efforts to half further nuclear
proliferation," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
However, it added, economic or trade-related measures have not
formed part of Australia's efforts.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, consistent with its concern for the well-being of the
people of Pakistan, it said, Australia will continue with its
small humanitarian assistance program in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Australian government has condemned Pakistan's decision to
undertake nuclear tests in the strongest possible terms, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
Quoting Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer, the
statement said a nuclear arms race in South Asia will exacerbate
rather than solve regional security tensions.
</P>
<P>
The statement also called on Pakistan and India to sign the
Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
