<HEADLINE> Styrofoam Tableware Banned on Yangtze Passenger Vessels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Communications has
issued an urgent circular ordering a halt to the use of styrofoam
tableware on all passenger vessels sailing on the
Yangtze River beginning July 1.
</P>
<P>
All the boats plying this largest river of the country
should start to use soluble paper-made table service to replace
the insoluble, disposable styrofoam ones, the notice says.
</P>
<P>
Pollution from disposal of styrofoam items is serious on the
river, despite the efforts of the Ministry of Communications, the
Ministry of Construction and the State Environmental Protection
Agency, who have jointly issued regulations on strengthening
control of garbage discharged by ships operating on the river.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Communications has demanded that boats be
equipped with enough garbage containers and separate rubbish
into different categories when collecting it.
</P>
<P>
Shipowners are now required to employ special stewards to make
sure that people do not throw garbage into the river. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
