<HEADLINE> 5 Killed, 20 Injured in Tehran Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The explosion at the Islamic
revolutionary court in northern Tehran on Tuesday killed five
people and injured 20 others, local newspaper Iran Daily on
Wednesday quoted witnesses as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, the death toll was not confirmed by official sources,
said the newspaper, which is run by the official news agency IRNA.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Tehran Radio reported on Tuesday that two were
killed and two others injured in the explosion which took place
at 1:45 p.m.local time (0915 GMT) in the waiting hall of the
court.
</P>
<P>
The News Radio, run by Tehran Radio, reported on Wednesday
that Iran's outlawed Mujahedin Khalq Organization (MKO) has
claimed responsibility for the explosion at the court, which deals
with cases related to arms and drug smuggling, anti-revolutionary
activities and issues threatening national security.
</P>
<P>
However, the IRNA Tuesday quoted an official from the court
public relations office as saying that the incident happened due
to negligence when explosives related to a case under
investigation were being carried to the court.
</P>
<P>
The MKO, Iran's largest armed opposition group, launched a
series of violent attacks on Iranian targets inside and outside
the country during the past decade, triggering a number of
cross-border raids by Tehran on the MKO bases near Iraqi capital
Baghdad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
