<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts Symposium on Sino-US Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 100 veteran diplomats and
specialists on international issues articulated their wish here
today that the coming visit of US President Bill Clinton will
further lead Sino-US relations toward a period of healthy and
positive development.
</P>
<P>
They said this at a symposium on Sino-US relations held by the
China Institute for International Strategic Studies (CIISS), where
former Chinese Ambassador to the US Li Daoyu delivered the keynote
speech.
</P>
<P>
Despite some existing divergences, they said, the two countries
have extensive and significant common interests. The establishment
of long-term, healthy and stable Sino-US relations not only
accords with the fundamental interests of the Chinese and
US peoples, but also serves to promote peace and development of
the world, they added.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit to the US last October
successfully enhanced mutual understanding, and accelerated
cooperation between the two countries, thus lifting Sino-US
relations to a new stage, they concluded.
</P>
<P>
A civilian academic group devoted to studies of international
issues, the CIISS has over the past 20 years played an active role
in improving Sino-US relations through exchanges and cooperation
with prestigious US institutes and scholars in the field. 
