<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Almost No Ecological Changes in Three Gorges Area" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The latest environmental monitoring
bulletin reports that the general ecology in the Three Gorges
Project area basically remained the same last year as the
year before.
</P>
<P>
"The effects of the project on the ecology and environment have
been mainly limited to the construction region, and no remarkable
damage has emerged," the bulletin says.
</P>
<P>
The bulletin, mainly compiled by the China Environmental
Monitoring Center, said that water and soil preservation and tree
planting efforts have greatly reduced the unfavorable impacts of
the project on the ecological environment.
</P>
<P>
The reservoir area near Chongqing has a forest coverage rate of
nearly 22 percent, and that in Hubei Province, 32 percent.
</P>
<P>
Rare and endangered aquatic animals, including the white-flag
dolphin and the Chinese sturgeon, have been protected in
regions affected by the Three Gorges Project, according to the
bulletin.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges and its surrounding area were hit by 93 minor
earthquakes measuring below 4.4 on the Richter scale last year,
which was similar to the situation the year before.
</P>
<P>
Seismic disaster prevention projects completed in the area have
greatly reduced losses caused by such phenomena as landslides and
mud-rock flows.
</P>
<P>
The bulletin says that although the water quality of the
mainstream of the Yangtze River is basically good, river sections
near cities have witnessed an obvious rise in pollution. It adds
that pollution accidents mainly caused by oil pollution happened
frequently last year, but were fewer compared with the year
before.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the density of suspended particles in the air was
rather serious around the project construction site.
</P>
<P>
China's environmental monitoring network in the Three Gorges
area has been keeping a close eye on the ecology and environment
in the area and the whole Yangtze River basin since 1996, and
since last year China has been issuing an annual bulletin on the
monitoring results. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
