<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Egyptian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading Egyptian newspapers on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Al-Ahram:
</P>
<P>
-- Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar is due to visit
Egypt late in June within a regional tour which will also take him
to Israel and the Palestinian areas. The visit is aimed at getting
fully acquainted with the latest peace process developments and
boosting the Egyptian-Spanish economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
Al-Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh telephoned Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak Tuesday night and the conversation covered
current situation in Arab world and the importance of securing
unified Arab attitude towards convening a plenary summit to
restore Arab solidarity to face challenges emerging from Israeli
hard-line policies.
</P>
<P>
Al Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- The Egyptian-Saudi higher joint committee meetings will open
in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, on June 24 on promoting trade exchange
and working out an investment protection plan.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- After talks with the visiting Israeli Defense Minister
Yitzhak Mordechai Tuesday on ways to reactivate the Mideast peace
process, Mubarak called for rendering the Middle East free of
weapons of mass destruction, adding there must be a world
principle for dismantling these weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
