<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Vietnam Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo
today met a Vietnamese delegation led by Nguyen Van Son, member of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam and
chairman of the Party's Commission for External Relations.
</P>
<P>
Wu, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), said that he
believed that the visit will further the relations between the two
parties and the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that the bilateral friendship is well grounded, adding
that more frequent exchanges will be beneficial to the development
of such ties.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier also briefed the visitors on China's domestic
economic situation, in particular the restructuring of state
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen highly praised China for its achievements in reforms and
opening-up.
</P>
<P>
This morning Nguyen held discussions with Dai Bingguo, head of
the International Department of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The seven-member delegation is here at the invitation of
the CPC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
