<DOCNO> XIE19980603.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE June 3 (Xinhua)-- The benchmark Straits Times
Industrial Index rebounded by 12 points on the Singapore Market to
close at 1219.80 on Wednesday from 1207.12 points on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 181.56 million units
valued at 219.66 million Singapore dollars (about 130.75 U.S.
dollars). Rises led falls by 227 t0 70, while 294 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Easyknit was once again the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 15.91 million units. It was followed by
Recpac which had 13.76 million shares traded. MBF Cap was next
with 10.25 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
CityDev and Venture led the gainers of the day as they rose by
50 cents to finish respectively at 5.80 and 4.68 Singapore
dollars. DBSF increased by 40 cents to end at 9.9 Singapore
dollars, taking the third place on the list of gainers.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, CityDev w98 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 94 cents to close at 2.98 Singapore dollars. Local
computer sound card maker Creative 50 fell by 60 cents to end at
30.80 Singapore dollars, while Asean lost 40 cents to finish at
6.50 U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
