<HEADLINE> China to Open New Air Routes to Paris, Okayama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- China Eastern Airlines announced
here today that it will open two new air routes -- one from
Shanghai to Okayama City in Japan on June 30, and the other from
Beijing, via Shanghai, to Paris on July 7.
</P>
<P>
"The opening of our sixth flight between Shanghai and Japan,
and fourth from Shanghai to Europe will contribute to the economic
and cultural exchanges among China, Japan and France." said the
president of the airline, Fu Yunbi.
</P>
<P>
Boeing MD-90 planes will be used on the twice-a-week flight
from Shanghai to Okayama, which will take about two hours, and
Airbus 340 planes will be used on the twice-a-week flight from
Beijing, via Shanghai, to Paris, which will take about 10 hours.
</P>
<P>
The Eastern Airlines, one of China's three biggest air
companies, at the moment has 120 domestic flights and 20
international ones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
