<DOCNO> XIE19980603.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Latest Environmental Situation Report (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- China's latest environmental
situation report says that the ecological environment in a number
of regions continued to deteriorate last year under the pressure
of population and economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The annual report, issued today by the State Environmental
Protection Administration, said China enhanced efforts for
pollution control in cities and major regions, and scored
remarkable achievements in the Huaihe River Valley.
</P>
<P>
"Some regions witnessed improved environmental quality
last year," said the report.
</P>
<P>
However, it pointed out that China's seven river systems,
lakes, reservoirs, underground water in some regions and some
coastal waters have suffered from pollution to varying degrees.
</P>
<P>
Many cities suffer from serious shortages of water, according
to the report, which added, "The shortage of water resources and
water pollution have restricted the country's economic and social
development."
</P>
<P>
China's air is still polluted mainly by sulphur dioxide, smoke
and dust. Central China and the southwestern part of the country
suffer greatly from acid rain.
</P>
<P>
With the faster urbanization, pollution caused by automobile
exhaust fumes has become serious in some big cities, although the
country's major urban air pollution problems are still sulphur
dioxide, smoke and dust, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Organic pollution is the main problem in urban water pollution,
and more cities are suffering from water shortages caused by
pollution.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980603.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Latest Environmental Situation Report (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Urban noise pollution has been turning serious, and so has the
garbage problem.
</P>
<P>
However, some medium and small cities have witnessed
improvements in the environment.
</P>
<P>
The report pointed out that both the quality and area of the
country's cultivated land have been decreasing, with the growth of
population and industry as well as the improper use of
agricultural chemicals.
</P>
<P>
"Too much land has been improperly used and wasted," it said.
</P>
<P>
The report said that China's forestry coverage rate was nearly 14
percent last year. However, grassland has degenerated because of
over-development, and biodiversity faces threats.
</P>
<P>
The country suffered from high temperatures last year and its
northern areas were hit by drought, affected by the unusually
strong El Nino, which was unfavorable to the country's
agriculture, the report added.
</P>
<P>
China issues its annual environmental situation report every
year before June 5, the World Environmental Day, in accordance
with its Environmental Protection Law, in a bid to increase
awareness of its environmental situation, improve the public's
environmental awareness, and promote international cooperation and
exchanges in the field.
</P>
<P>
The national data in the report do not cover Hong Kong, Taiwan
or Macao.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
