<DOCNO> XIE19980603.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Signs Air Services Agreement With Luxembourg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) signed here on Wednesday an air
services agreement with the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg.
</P>
<P>
HKSAR Secretary for Economic Services Stephen Ip and
Luxembourg's Minister of Communications and Transport Mady
Delvaux-Stehres signed the accord on behalf of their respective
governments. The prime minister of Luxembourg, Jean-Claude
Juncker, was present on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
"Air cargo transport provides an important link between Hong
Kong and Luxembourg," Ip said while speaking at the signing
ceremony. "Our aviation relations date back to 1972, when Cargolux
started all-cargo services to Hong Kong. Since then Cargolux has
been playing an important role in promoting our bilateral trade."
</P>
<P>
"The signing of the air services agreement opens a new chapter
in the economic and aviation relations between Hong Kong and
Luxembourg. I look forward to the continued growth of the
bilateral relations in the years to come," he said.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR/Luxembourg agreement is the 29th air services
agreement signed by Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
