<HEADLINE> HK Approves Disaster Relief Fund Grant for Filipino Drought Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Disaster Relief Fund Advisory
Committee of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region has
approved a grant of 0.35 million HK dollars (0.04 million U.S.
dollars) to Oxfam Hong Kong which will extend the emergency relief
for the drought victims in Mindanao, the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The nine-member committee chaired by Chief Secretary for
Administration Anson Chan is concerned about the hardship
suffered by the drought victims in Mindanao, the Philippines and
it hopes that the grant can help to provide some immediate relief
to those affected. 
