<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Not to Resume N-Testing: Jiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
that China opposes all nuclear tests and will not resume such
tests itself.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark when meeting with Jean Miot, president
of Agence France Presse, here today.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question on whether China would resume nuclear
testing, following the suit of India and Pakistan, he noted that
China opposes the nuclear arms race in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
"We oppose the nuclear tests conducted by India and have
expressed serious regret over the nuclear tests carried out
by Pakistan. However, India originated the tense situation
in the region," Jiang pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He said that even though China has nuclear weapons, it is
committed to not using nuclear weapons first, and advocates the
complete prohibition and thorough destruction of nuclear
weapons. "China will not resume nuclear testing," he reiterated.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
