<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drunken Philippine Cop Shoots Dead 2 Colleagues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A drunken policemen went berserk and
indiscriminately fired his rifle inside a camp in the central
Philippines Monday, killing two fellow cops, a police report
available here said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report said the police officer, 45, apparently angered by
his financial problems, ran amuck and shot with an M-16 Armalite
at two other cops Monday night inside the mobile police head
office in a village in Ibahay, Aklan province.
</P>
<P>
It was the second shooting incident inside camps in a week, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Four soldiers, including a navy officer, were killed in a
gunfight inside the military's general headquarters at Camp
Aguinaldo north of Manila on May 27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
