<DOCNO> XIE19980603.0150 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index rose 5.75
points to 526.36, the all-share Emas Index added 1.47 points to
134.48, the Industrial Index was 10.46 points higher at 1,022.81
while the Second Board Index gained 0.70 of a point to 111.19.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers by 394 to 173 while 171 counters were
unchanged and 180 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was 126.114 million shares worth 267.434
million ringgit (68.2229 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board volume increased to 115.654 million shares
valued at 251.621 million ringgit (64.189 million U.S. dollars)
from Tuesday's 101.759 million shares worth 231.939 million
ringgit (59.1681 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board rose to 10.460 million shares valued at 15.812
million ringgit (4.0336 million U.S. dollars) against 9.344
million shares worth 14.713 million ringgit (3.7533 million U.S.
dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals expanded to 5.112 million shares valued at
18.607 million ringgit (about 4.7466 million U.S. dollars) from
2.150 million shares worth 6.437 million ringgit (1.642 million
U.S. dollars) on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
