<HEADLINE> Canadian Naval Vessels Visit Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Two Canadian naval vessels arrived
in Shanghai today to begin a six-day official friendly visit to
China.
</P>
<P>
Commanded by Rear Admiral R. D. Buck, commander of the Pacific
Ocean Fleet of the Canadian Navy, the ships form the third Canadian
naval visit to China, after one to Shanghai in 1983 and another to
Qingdao in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Hou Xiyue, commander of the Shanghai Navy Base of the
Chinese People's Liberation Army, hosted a welcoming ceremony
here today.
</P>
<P>
The guided missile escort vessel "HMCS Vancouver" and the
supply escort "HMCS Protecteur" have on board 452 officers and men.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Canadian Ambassador to China Howard Balloch and
military attache Captain Hans W. Etzel, Buck also met with
officials from the municipal government as well as other Chinese
naval officers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
