<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Earmarks 18 Billion Yuan For Housing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has so far collected 18
billion yuan in public funds for house building, accounting for
one fifth of the nation's total for this sector.
</P>
<P>
The city began to accumulate public funds for housing
construction in 1991, to enable local workers and employees to buy
houses.
</P>
<P>
The money was accumulated from 3.91 million local workers as
well as from the units and organizations they work for.
</P>
<P>
Some 700,000 families have bought their own apartments by
drawing money from this fund.  
</P>
</TEXT>
