<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New-Design Buildings Survive Quake Tremors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Some 25,000 quake-proof
housing units built in areas hit by earthquakes early this year
all survived the two moderate aftershocks which occurred there
Tuesday morning, Zhangbei County, Hebei Province, officials said
today in this capital of the province.
</P>
<P>
No one was killed or injured in the two aftershocks, both over
4 degrees on the Richter Scale, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the shocks did not damage the buildings built after
the earthquake measuring 6.2 degrees on the Richter Scale on
January 10, they said.
</P>
<P>
That strong tremor destroyed more than 16,800 housing units,
accounting for over 70 percent of the total in the county. 
</P>
</TEXT>
