<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The following are the major news
items in leading French newspapers on Wednesday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- Russian Prime Minister Sergei Kiriyenko will begin a
two-day official visit to France which is aimed at acquiring an
international credibility for his country facing a financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
-- The Algerian security services Tuesday announced the death
of the chief of the Armed Islamic Group (GIA), Mohamed Kebaili,
also known as "Ayachi", during an operation against the GIA in the
suburb of Algiers.
</P>
