<HEADLINE> At Least 21 Killed in Landslide in India's Assam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- At least 21 people were killed
and nine others injured in a landslide triggered by heavy rains in
Assam state's Cachar district, eastern India, Wednesday, official
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers have pulled 18 bodies out of the rubble of
thatched huts of the victims and search was on for three more
victims.
</P>
<P>
This is one of the worst landslides in recent years in the
state. The victims, mostly tea garden laborers dwelling on a
hillock, were buried alive when torrential rains and high velocity
winds razed to the ground mud-built thatched huts along the
hillside adjoining the Chandighat tea estate.
</P>
<P>
The casualties were feared to be higher as searchers went on to
recover the bodies, the sources said. 
</P>
