<HEADLINE> Macao, Zhuhai To Start Construction of Joint Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a bridge connecting
Macao and Zhuhai in south China's Guangdong province will start
later this month, the Sino-Portuguese Infrastructure Coordination
Commission (SPICC) has decided.
</P>
<P>
The commission will hold a ribbon-cutting ceremony for the
launch of the bridge at the end of June, said a press communique
issued Tuesday following the commission's two-day plenary session.
</P>
<P>
The planned bridge, scheduled to be completed before the
handover next year, will open up a new passage between Macao and
Zhuhai apart from the current land border gate.
</P>
<P>
"It will help improve Macao's outward land transportation
conditions and facilitate the development of Macao's islands and
Zhuhai's Hengqin Island," said Xie Houhe, chief of the Chinese
side of the commission.
</P>
<P>
With a planned investment of more than 200 million patacas
(about 25 million U.S. dollars), the bridge will be 1.3 kilometers
long with six traffic lanes. It is 22 meters high above the water
surface.
</P>
<P>
The investment will be shared equally by Macao and Zhuhai. Each
side is responsible for the construction of its part of the
bridge. It will be managed by governments of both sides and will
be toll free for traffic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
