<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The number of personal
bankruptcies in the United States reached a record high during the
year ending on March 31, according to the statistics released
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Americans filed nearly 342,000 personal bankruptcy petitions in
the first quarter and the total petitions were nearly 1.37 million
by the end of March, a record for any 12-month period, the
Bankruptcy Issues Council (BIC) said in a statement.
</P>
