<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Offers Help to the Disabled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- As many as 42,000 disabled people of
various ethnic groups have shaken off poverty in the Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region, thanks to the regional government's
arduous efforts.
</P>
<P>
An employment insurance fund of more than 16 million yuan
(about two million US dollars) has been set up in the autonomous
region, and more than 3,400 disabled people have received
employment trainings.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that among the 540,000 disabled people in
Xinjiang, 200,000 are living in poverty, one fifth of the
region's poverty-stricken population.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, local governments at all levels have increased
poverty-relief input and promulgated laws and regulations to
safeguard the interests of the disabled.
</P>
<P>
Preferential policies have also been carried out in rural
areas, which have saved the disabled people 21 million yuan of
various fee charges.
</P>
<P>
Memet Niyaz, a farmer in Turpan who has two disabled family
members, set up a paint plant with financial support from the
local disabled federation. With annual production of over 400
tons, the plant generates more than 80,000 net profits each year,
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
