<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China City's Border Trade with Russia Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Heihe City in Northeast China's
Heilongjiang Province conducted more than 70 million US
dollars-worth of border trade with Russia during the January-April
period this year, a big rise from the figure for the same period
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
And the number of domestic and overseas visitors to the city
reached 30,900 during the four-month period.
</P>
<P>
This is a result of local efforts to improve the facilities at
the Heihe port of entry, the first border city of its kind in
China to be opened to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
International, non-governmental and border trade is dealt with
at the multi-functional port of entry.
</P>
<P>
The booming border trade has helped give a big boost to
economic growth in Heihe, which has improved its information,
technology, finance and commodity networks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
