<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 125 Coma Patients Recover in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- At least 125 people who were
comatose in northeast China's Heilongjiang province have recovered
the ability to speak and move, and even take care of themselves.
</P>
<P>
Of them, four have returned to normal life and 29 have generally
recovered.
</P>
<P>
In 1991, doctors in the Heilongjiang Province Recovery Hospital
developed a special treatment for people who were injured in
various accidents.
</P>
<P>
They have treated comatose patients with a combination of
hyperbaric oxygenation, surgery, physiotherapy, acupuncture, and
massage.
</P>
<P>
The doctors say they usually bring the patients back to
consciousness within 40 days, even in seven days.
</P>
<P>
Most of the patients have lost consciousness and cannot move at
all except for the eyes. Doctors worldwide still have no effective
cure for such patients and some countries even opt for
euthanasia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
