<HEADLINE> Scientific Research Important for China in 21st Century (part 1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Zhou Guangzhao, a prominent
physicist who is Vice-Chairman of China's National People's
Congress Standing Committee, has told an academic congress of the
Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) that scientists need to be
innovative and pioneering to support industrial development at the
turn of the new century.
</P>
<P>
Zhou, who is president of the China Association for Science and
Technology, said that the 21st century will be a knowledge-backed
era and listed some major discoveries of Chinese scientists,
especially in physics.
</P>
<P>
He said that Europe is building a large accelerator with
billions of U.S. dollars, but that China built an
electron-positron collider with much less money. The Beijing
collider is the best accelerator for research on charms, the basic
unit for forming an atom and a neutron. The U.S. has decided to
suspend work at an accelerator at Harvard and has asked some
scientists to work in China, Zhou says.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chinese scientists have shown how gravity pulled
the earth and the sun together and how gluons link up fundamental
particles. ( more)

nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
