<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drinking Water Quality Improved in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Drinking water quality in Xi'an,
capital of northwest China's Shaanxi Province, has been improved,
with all the city's water source qualities having passed
standards, the city's environmental protection bureau said.
</P>
<P>
Priority has been given to the environmental protection over
the city's drinking water sources and relevant regulations have
also been worked out.
</P>
<P>
More than 258 polluting enterprises located around the
protection zone of the city's water resources have been closed
down or relocated and 179 low-level refineries have been shut down.
</P>
<P>
To deal with worsening water shortage caused by rapid economic
development, the city has launched a series of water-supply
projects. After the completion of the Heihe river aqueduction
project, an on-going 2.5 billion-yuan(about 300 million US
dollars) project, the city's water supply capacity will rise to
more than 1.72 million cubic meters each day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
