<HEADLINE> Scientific Research Important for China in 21st Century (part 2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhou said he believes that China is out in front superconductor
research and was only three months behind Japan in magnet
discoveries, and that the U.S.'s General Motors has transferred
its permanent magnet work to a CAS company.
</P>
<P>
Also, many top laboratories are buying nonlinear optical
crystals from China.
</P>
<P>
Zhou also mentioned important discoveries in other fields, like
the technique that uses highly poisonous white arsenic to treat
leukaemia and other kinds of cancers. Because of molecular
studies, Chinese scientists found that the white arsenic can alter
chromosomes.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that, although China lags behind some
developed countries in the field of microelectronics, it can
develop new products with advanced chips from abroad, and a CAS
lab has developed a kind of telephone black box for Internet users.
</P>
<P>
He said that knowledge is shared by all of mankind in a
knowledge economy, but that China can only catch up with the rest
of the world by inventing things after using foreign ideas.
</P>
</TEXT>
