<HEADLINE> Sea Tunnel in China's Bohai Bay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists say that a
57-kilometer tunnel should be built in Bohai Bay to link the
Shangdong and Liaodong peninsulas.
</P>
<P>
The idea was put forth at a seminar held recently on using
subterranean space in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The tunnel would greatly shorten the distance between northeast
China and eastern and northern China and would help the balanced
development of the regional economy, "Economic Reference Daily"
quoted the scientists as saying.
</P>
<P>
They say that subterranean space should be combined with urban
development.
</P>
<P>
A seabed tunnel should also be built in the Qiongzhou Strait,
connecting the Leizhou Peninsula, in Guangdong Province, with the
island province of Hainan.
</P>
<P>
Subway construction should be one of the key projects of this
space utilization program in the next century also. 
</P>
</TEXT>
