<HEADLINE> Good Grain Harvest in Sight in Tianjin Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- North China's Tianjin Municipality
is expected to reap a wheat harvest of more than 700,000 tons from
its 150,000 hectares of wheatfields this year, according to an
official forecast.
</P>
<P>
The predicated yield is about the same as last year's actual
figure and the second largest ever. Currently, ripening wheat crop
is doing fine on an area of 150,000 ha.
</P>
<P>
"Barring severe natural adversities in the days ahead, there
will be good wheat yields," a city official said, adding that the
recent rainfalls are helpful to growing wheat.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin is one of China's four leading municipalities directly
under the jurisdiction of the central government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
