<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Market Keeps Rising Momentum in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Market
continued to move up steadily in May, with the major market
indicator hitting a one-year high.
</P>
<P>
The Composite Index of the Shanghai Stock Exchange opened in
May at 1,353.05 points and ended the month at 1,411.2 points, a
one-year high, rising slightly most of the time. The month ending
was 5.79 percent higher than the finishing level of April.
</P>
<P>
The May stock turnover, however, shrank nearly 10 percent from
April to 155.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Stocks of companies undergoing asset restructuring continued to
be the market leaders last month, with Qinggong Jixie up more than
60 percent on a monthly basis. Other significantly rising stocks
included Lianhe Industrial, up 30 percent, and Yanzhong
Industrial, up 23 percent.
</P>
<P>
In contrast to the rising market for A-shares, referring to
those for domestic investors, the market index of B-shares, which
are reserved for overseas investors, dived in May,
from 51.52 points at the start of the month to 46.01 points at the
end of it. The end position was ten percent down from a month
previously.
</P>
<P>
The treasury bond market also rose in May, with spot-bond
turnover surging 27.6 percent on a monthly basis to more than 40.1
billion yuan. The month's turnover of bond repurchasing contracts
was worth 132.8 billion yuan, up 3.3 percent from the previous
month.
</P>
<P>
Also in May, the fund market was activated by the listing of
China's third securities investment fund -- Fund Xinghua. The
month's total fund transaction reached 12.1 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
