<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping Theory Popular Among East China College Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Six students in the History
Department of Yangzhou University, in east China's Jiangsu Province,
have written 80 articles on the study of Deng Xiaoping Theory in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
And, by the end of April, the province's universities and
colleges had had 2,178 student associations, with 60,000 members,
studying Deng Xiaoping Theory. The first was set up in Nanjing
University, one of China's major universities, in September, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The associations invite renowned economists and socialists to
lecture and have had a series of campaigns in Nanjing, the capital
of Jiangsu, to teach the spirit of Deng Xiaoping Theory to
ordinary citizens.
</P>
<P>
Other universities have held a variety of activities like
contests, debates, and study tours of prosperous regions that have
greatly benefited from Deng Xiaoping Theory. 
