Shanghai Charity Fund, which has donated more than 25.8 million
yuan (3.1 million US dollars) for the elderly charity activities
since its founding four years ago.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is one of the first Chinese cities which are becoming
increasingly ageing. It has 2.34 million people at and above the
age of 60, who make up 18.2 percent of the municipality's total
population. 
