<HEADLINE> Man Recovers From Coma In East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A man who was in a coma for nearly
half a year and had been declared a hopeless case by doctors, has
regained consciousness in a hospital in the Chinese city of
Nanjing recently.
</P>
<P>
Forty-year-old Wang Chang had received a traumatic head injury
in a fight with some robbers a few years ago. His life had been
saved, but the injury left him in a coma.
</P>
<P>
After five months, he was sent to the Nanjing Naval Medical
Center for further treatment. Wang is one of several people who
have recovered from a coma in the hospital, where doctors have
used electric impulses to stimulate spinal nerves.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, the center has treated 103 persons who
were in a coma, with 80 of them regaining some feeling in their
limbs.
</P>
<P>
Pan Min, who received a head injury in a traffic accident,
regained his ability to speak after spending ten months in a coma,
and is now able to do simple exercises and sing short bits of
songs.
</P>
<P>
Every year, about 100,000 people become comatose in China
because of a variety of accidents.  
</P>
</TEXT>
