<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Million People Live in Slums in Dhaka: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- At least two million people are
living in slums in Bangladesh's capital city of Dhaka, national
news agency BSS reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Dhaka's population is nine million and it may shoot up to
nearly 20 million by the year 2020 due to the present trend of
urban population increase by 10 percent a year, a report of the
Habitat Council of Bangladesh was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Dhaka's population in 1951 was only 3.36 million, in 1991 it
was seven million and in 1998 it stands at nine million. The
present rate of urban population increase is as high as five
percent in Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
Along with the increase of Dhaka's population, the number of
slum-dwellers would be around 10 million by the year 2020 in Dhaka
city alone, the report predicted.
</P>
<P>
Problems in the slums are already acute due to lack of minimum
facilities needed for livelihood, the report pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi government has attached great importance to
reducing the number of city slum-dwellers by implementing several
projects with assistance from international bodies and agencies
including the United Nations Development Program and the Asian
Development Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
