<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With AFP President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin today
expressed his hope that the Agence France Presse (AFP) would
introduce China in a more comprehensive and objective manner to
give the world a better understanding of the country.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks during a meeting with visiting AFP
President Jean Miot here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that AFP is one of the major news agencies in the
West and China attaches importance to AFP's influence in world
media.
</P>
<P>
He said Sino-French relations have witnessed a good momentum of
development in recent years, and French President Jacques Chirac
and he have established a good personal relationship.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government is ready to work with its French
counterpart to constantly advance bilateral ties, and this is in
line with the interest of both sides and world peace, stability
and development, Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president also answered questions raised by Miot
concerning Sino-US relations, the situation in south Asia and the
financial crisis in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Noting that AFP is the earliest news agency in the world, Miot
said AFP and himself hold a strong feeling and friendship towards
China.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation between AFP and the Chinese side, especially
China's Xinhua News Agency, has registered positive achievements
over the past years with the efforts from both sides, Miot told
Jiang, adding that AFP hopes to further enhance its ties with the
Chinese side. 
</P>
