<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Exports Grow 16.75 Pct in 10 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's exports registered a
16.75 percent growth in the first 10 months of the current fiscal
year (July 1997-June 1998), The Financial Express daily reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Total export earnings in the July-April period stood at 4.17
billion U.S. dollars as against 3.57 billion dollars in the same
period of the last fiscal year, and the export of industrial goods
increased by 19.6 percent while that of primary goods declined by
