<HEADLINE> Djukanovic's Coalition Wins Montenegro Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Montenegrin President Milo
Djukanovic's Coalition for Better Life won the parliamentary
elections this past weekend, unofficial results reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The media here said the results are unofficial because voting
has to be repeated for some 1,262 voters in two polling
stations. The official results are expected to be announced on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
However, according to votes already counted, Djukanovic's
coalition will receive 42 seats in the 78-seat parliament, and the
Socialist People's Party 29 seats.
</P>
<P>
