rival, Momir Bulatovic, who is the former Montenegrin president
and now prime minister of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia consists of two republics, Montenegro and Serbia.
</P>
<P>
Also on Tuesday, Djukanovic issued a statement saying he hoped
Federal President Slobodan Milosevic would accept the results of
the election.
</P>
<P>
It is widely believed the U.S.-backed Djukanovic's victory over
the pro-Belgrade Bulatovic will have a far-reaching influence upon
the political situation in both Montenegro and Yugoslavia. 
