<HEADLINE> 12 Killed in Road Accidents in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 people were killed and
192 injured Tuesday in five road accidents in Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
The road accidents occurred on the same day in southeastern
districts of Hajiganj and Khagrachari, western district of Pabna,
southwestern port city of Chittagong and northeastern district of
Brahmanbaria, press reports Wednesday quoted police sources as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Four persons were killed and 60 others injured Tuesday in a
road accident on Dhaka-Sylhet highway when a Dhaka-bound passenger
bus from Sylhet collided with a Sylhet-bound bus from Comilla.
</P>
<P>
Four people were killed and 52 others injured on the same day
when a Shahzadpur-bound bus collided head on with a truck in
Pabna.
</P>
<P>
Two persons were killed and 15 others injured when a passenger
bus rammed some roadside shops Tuesday on the Chittagong-Cox's
Bazar road.
</P>
<P>
Another two people were killed and 25 others injured when a
Sylhet-bound bus fell into a roadside ditch on Dhaka-Sylhet
highway.
</P>
<P>
At least 40 persons were also injured when two passenger-jeeps
collided on Khagrachari-Rangamati road.
</P>
<P>
The injured passengers were admitted to nearby hospitals for
treatment after the accidents took place, and police seized
several vehicles but some drivers had fled, according to the
police sources. 
</P>
