<HEADLINE> India's Heat Wave Toll Reaches 1,359 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The death toll in the heat wave
sweeping across India this summer had risen to 1,359 by Tuesday,
press reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The worst hit was India's eastern coastal state of Orissa,
where the death toll was put at 649 though the government
maintained the toll at 380.
</P>
<P>
In Andhra state in southern India, 131 more people died in the
intense heat wave in the state, bringing the toll to 363. The
scorching heat wave continued to prevail in Punjab, Haryana and
Uttar Pradesh states with temperatures well over 45 degrees
Centigrade.
</P>
<P>
Apart from Orissa and Andhra Pradesh, which were worst hit in
the heat wave, Rajasthan state has recorded 142 deaths followed
by Uttar Pradesh (83), Madhya Pradesh (29), Bihar (30),
Maharashtra (25), Gujarat (12), West Bengal (10), Punjab (9) and
Tamil Nadu (1).
</P>
<P>
According to another report, over 100 people have died in the
heat wave in New Delhi, capital of India, in the past few weeks.
</P>
