<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Telecom Sector Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The telecommunications industry in
this east China metropolis generated more than 4.6 billion yuan in
output value during the first quarter of this year, a 29 percent
rise over the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The industry saw a 41 percent rise in sales and a nearly 100
percent increase in pre-tax profits over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The hi-tech industry turns out a large number of products,
including numerically program-controlled switchboards, optic-fiber
lines and cables, SDH transmission equipment, fax machines and
intelligent cards.
</P>
<P>
The output of numerically program-controlled switchboards in the
city during the first quarter of this year rose 37 percent over
the 1997 level.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai-Bell Telephone Equipment Manufacturing Company, a
Sino-Belgian joint venture, invested nearly 400 million yuan in
technology development last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a center to develop telecom technology has been set
up in the city, at a cost of 18 million US dollars.  
</P>
