<HEADLINE> Inflation Up in Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Czech Republic's inflation in
the first quarter of this year rose to 13 percent, said a report
of the Czech National Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
While inflation increased, the average salary of workers
rose by only 10.9 percent compared with the same period last
year, a drop of 2.1 percent in real terms, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Rising inflation weakened purchasing power and retail sales
kept dropping in the first three months this year.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the decrease in real income is the result
of a tighter economic policy adopted by the Czech government and
its failure to control inflation. 
</P>
