<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Revenue from merchandise exports for
the first four months of 1998 remained on the upswing by posting a
19.9 percent growth to 9.1 billion U.S. dollars from 7.6 billion
dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Data from the National Statistics Office showed Wednesday that
for April 1998, aggregate receipts also grew by 9.8 percent to 2.3
billion dollars from 2.1 billion dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
