month which accounted for 53 percent of aggregate receipts, grew
by 31.7 percent to 1.2 billion dollars from 919.9 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Accounting for 88 percent of the aggregate, manufactured goods,
the biggest commodity group, posted a 16.4 percent rise in revenue
as sales amounted to 2.0 billion dollars, up from 1.7 billion
dollars a year earlier, the data showed.
</P>
<P>
Exports to the United States, accounting for 34.2 percent of
the total, posted a 10.3 percent increase, reaching 780.7 million
dollars from 708.1 million dollars a year earlier. 
