<HEADLINE> Indonesian Parliament to Meet Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's House of
Representatives (DPR) will hold a plenary meeting next month to
discuss plans to hold an extraordinary meeting of the People's
Consultative Assembly (MPR), The Indonesian Observer Wednesday
quoted an official as saying.
</P>
<P>
"We will discuss plans to hold an extraordinary meeting of the
MPR at the end of this year or early next year," Deputy House
Speaker Hari Sabarno said after a meeting of the House leaders
here Tuesday.
