extraordinary meeting of the MPR by the end of this year prior to
the holding of an accelerated general elections early next year.
</P>
<P>
Sabarno said the extraordinary MPR meeting will mainly revise
the Broad Guidelines of State Policy which stipulate that the
nation will not hold a general election until 2002.
</P>
<P>
