<HEADLINE> British Prime Minister to Visit Sweden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, June 2 (Xinhua)-- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
will visit Sweden on June 8.
</P>
<P>
Blair, the current president of the European Union (EU), will
also go to Denmark and Finland to prepare for the June 15-16 EU
summit meeting in Cardiff, Britain.
</P>
<P>
The British prime minister is expected to meet with his Swedish
counterpart Goeran Persson next Monday to discuss urgent EU
issues, such as the creation of jobs and EU's eastward expansion.
</P>
</TEXT>
