<DOCNO> XIE19980603.0285 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Austria Urges All-Out Effort to Tackle EU's Unemployment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- European Union states should give
top priority to reducing unemployment, especially among young
people, Austrian Chancellor Viktor Klima said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Describing the EU's high jobless rate as its "biggest mistake",
Klima told a meeting of international financial experts that there
was no "all-purpose key" to lowering unemployment.
</P>
<P>
Employment policies had to be coordinated on all levels --
within each state, Europe and the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
The EU summit later this month will discuss employment plans of
member states, while the summit scheduled for the end of the year
is expected to comment and make amendments to the policies of EU
members.
</P>
<P>
Klima warned election results of some countries highlighted the
political need for better employment as jobless young people
without hope were more susceptible to extreme rightism.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance of setting up a European social
model and called for the reestablishment of welfare states.
</P>
<P>
On the EU's enlargement, Klima said that Austria, with the
longest border line with eastern Europe, was especially concerned
about expansion.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the expansion should avoid the unprepared opening
of borders which would lead to panic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
