<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Unemployed to Increase to 15.4 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of the unemployed in
Indonesia is expected to increase to 15.4 million at the end of
this year, a government official was quoted by local press
Wednesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
The figure, representing 17.1 percent of the country's 90
million work force, was revised upward from previous estimates of
13.4 million because of a predicted contraction in the economy,
Manpower Minister Fahmi Idris said.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bureau of Statistics announced Monday that the
country's economy is expected to shrink 10.1 percent in 1998 due
to the economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
"If the damage to the economy becomes worse, unemployment
figures will increase," the minister warned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
