<HEADLINE> Hingis, Seles Enter Semi-finals at French Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- World women's top player Martina
Hingis of Switzerland showed her prowess at the French Open here
on Tuesday, while former No. 1 Monica Seles came back to enter the
semi-fanals.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old Hingis, beaten in last year's final by Croatian
Iva Majoli, never gave Venus Williams a chance to turn the
situation. Hingis triumphed 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
American Williams has now lost six of her eight encounters with
Hingis.
</P>
<P>
Hingis will clash with three-time champion Seles, who played
her first tournament since the death of her father last month,
rallied to beat Jana Novotna of the Czech Republic 4-6, 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In the other women's match, Arantxa Sanchez Vicario, who swept
past 19-year-old Patty Schynder 6-2, 6-7 (5-7), 6-0, will meet
second-seed Lindsay Davenport of the United States, who advanced
with a 6-1, 5-7, 6-3 victory over Majoli.
</P>
<P>
In the men's play, Spain's Carlos Moya dashed third seed
Marcelo Rios's dream to ratain the men's No.1 ranking in 6-1, 2-6,
6-4.
</P>
<P>
Moya now plays compatriot Felix Mantilla, who earlier beat 1995
champion Thomas Muster of Austria 6-4, 6-2, 4-6, 6-3.  
</P>
</TEXT>
