<HEADLINE> More Overseas Investments to Coastal Province of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Fujian Provincial government
approved the establishment of 686 foreign-funded enterprises in
the first four months of this year, 4.5 percent down from last
year's same period.
</P>
<P>
However, the amount of contractual value climbed to 1.231 billion
U.S. dollars, up 5.1 percent over the same period of last
year. The amount of funds used in the first four months of
this year totaled 1.297 billion U.S. dollars, a 0.2-percent rise.
</P>
<P>
Of the new firms, 160 were funded by Taiwan, representing a 32
percent rise compared with a year ago. They involved a contractual
value of 177 million U.S. dollars, up 35 percent over last year's
same period.
</P>
<P>
Local analysts say that the growth of investment from Taiwan
was led by a relaxed situation between the two sides of the Taiwan
Straits, well performance of Taiwan-funded firms and
improved investment environment in Fujian.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
