<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Firms to Install Microwave Link in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Two Japanese firms have agreed with
the Myanmar communications authorities to install a new digital
microwave link in Myanmar, official newspaper The New Light of
Myanmar reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the credit agreement and supply contract reached here
Tuesday among the state-run Myanmar Posts and Telecommunications,
the Pujitsu Ltd. and the Daimaru Inc. of Japan, the two Japanese
firms will supply equipment to the Myanmar side to install the new
link between the capital of Yangon and the second largest city of
Mandalay along the west bank of the Ayeyawaddy River.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese firms will also join in setting up similar links
in the country's border areas, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has introduced the microwave link system in the country
since 1995 to ensure smooth and direct trunk call between the
capital and major towns in the border areas. So far the capital
city has been able to link with nine other cities through the
system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
