<HEADLINE> Spain to Provide $40-Million Loan to Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Spain will provide a 40 million
U.S. dollar loan to Nicaragua in order to help the country
purchase goods and services, the Nicaraguan journal La Prensa
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The loan was negotiated by Nicaraguan President Arnoldo Aleman
and Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar during his visit to
Nicaragua last year.
</P>
<P>
Nicaraguan Minister of Foreign Cooperation David Robleto, who
went to Spain last week to complete the negotiations, said the
interest on the 40-million dollar loan was much lower than others
offered by local markets.
</P>
<P>
Robleto said his visit to Spain was aimed at following up on
agreements signed by the Nicaragua president and the Spanish prime
minister last year. 
</P>
