<HEADLINE> 18 Killed In Train-Bus Collision in Indonesia's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- An express train Tuesday collided
with a bus near Demak, a town in Indonesia's Central Java, killing
18 persons, according to reports reaching here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The train which was on its way from Jakarta to Surabaya,
capital of East Java province, hit the bus at an unguarded
crossing where it had stopped because of engine trouble at noon.
</P>
<P>
The bus with its 18 passengers was thrown tens of meters away.
It was one of four vehicles carrying a group of villagers
returning from a condolence visit to another village, the reports
said. 
</P>
