<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, June 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. space shuttle Discovery was sent into space
Tuesday evening from Kennedy Space Center, Cape Canaveral,Flo.,
carrying with it six crew members and the Alpha Magnetic
Spectrometer designed and made by scientists from China, the
United States and other countries.
</P>
<P>
During its 10-day space trip, the space shuttle will for the
first time place the Alpha Magnetic Spectrometer, a 3.5 ton
particle detector, into space and carry out high energy physics
experiments. (US-Space Shuttle-Launching)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa said Tuesday the
upcoming summit of the Organization of the African Unity will seek
ways to settle disputes through peaceful means and maintain peace
on the continent.
</P>
<P>
Moussa, who will lead Egypt's delegation to a ministerial
meeting and the summit held in Burkina Faso on June 4-10, told
reporters that political and security problems in Africa will top
the agenda of the summit.
</P>
<P>
Despite the problems in Africa's political, economic and social
situations, Moussa said, the continent still boasts successes as
"a general economic growth indicates progress." (Egypt-African
Summit)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- Greece and the United States Tuesday began a two-day
joint military exercises as part of their efforts to strengthen
the military ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The exercises, codenamed "Alexander the Great'98", is being
conducted in the Greek area of the Pagasitikos gulf, Skiros and
the northeast Aegean Sea, according to the semi-official Athens
News Agency (ANA). (Greece-US-War Games)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The Palestinian National Authority (PNA) Tuesday
brushed off an Israeli criticism of a proposed Arab Summit, saying
the summit only responds to Arab will to salvage the Mideast peace.
</P>
<P>
"Holding an Arab Summit is to free the peace process of the
deadly shackles placed by the incumbent Israeli leadership," PNA
chief delegate to the Arab League Mohamed Sobeih told Egypt's
Middle East News Agency.
</P>
<P>
"It is exclusively an internal affair of the Arabs that does
not need permission from anyone else," he said. (PNA-Arab Summit)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- An intergovernmental agreement on plutonium was
signed here by Russia, Germany and France on Tuesday, according to
Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the Russian nuclear power plants will be
able to use the plutonium obtained from dismantled nuclear
warheads and no longer needed for the country's defense.
(Russia-Germany-France-Plutonium) 
</P>
