that the inclusion of Eguavon into the final 22-man squad was
informed to the Nigeria Football Association (NFA) at 14:00 A.M.,
Tuesday afternoon by Milutinovic.
</P>
<P>
Milutinovic, in a fax he sent to the NFA from the team's camp
in Zurich, Switzerland, confirmed that the 22-man list has been
submitted to the Federation of International Football Associations
(FIFA).
</P>
<P>
Milutinovic had sent a 21-man list to the NFA Monday afternoon,
but said that he would make up his mind between Mobi Oparaku and
Austin Eguavon by Tuesday, to meet the deadline set by the FIFA
for teams to submit their final lists of 22 players.
