<HEADLINE> Technology Shares Rebound in New York </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Technology stocks on Wall Street
rose sharply Tuesday, but the broad market again made little
progress.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average kept a marginal gain with
about an hour left to the session, but finished 31.13 lower at
8,891.24.
</P>
<P>
The technology-laden Nasdaq composite index wiped out nearly
half of Monday's 32-point plunge, rising 14.97 to 1,761.79.
</P>
<P>
Even with Tuesday's gains, the Nasdaq composite sits about 150
points, or 8 percent, below April 22's closing record of 1,917.61.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a slim margin on the
New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 rose 2.05 to 1,093.03, and the NYSE
composite index rose 0.21 to 565.35.
</P>
<P>
But the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 1.47 to
449.70, and the smaller-company dominated American Stock Exchange
composite index fell 1.21 to 706.30. 
</P>
