<HEADLINE> Chrysler Reports Best Month Ever in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Chrysler Corp., the third largest
automaker in the U.S., reported the best domestic sales month in
its 73-year history in May.
</P>
<P>
The company sold more than 250,000 vehicles in May in the
United States, a monthly record ever set.
</P>
<P>
The American automaker reported Tuesday that the number of
vehicles it sold last month rose 27 percent from the year before.
Vans, pickups and sport utility vehicles surged 39 percent; cars
rose 5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The increase was attributed to the strong economy and the boom
on Wall Street, as well as price deduction and other incentives.
</P>
<P>
General Motors Corp. and Ford Motor Co. are also expected to
report strong May sales Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Among other automakers, Honda Motor Co. also set a May record
as U.S. sales grew 18 percent. Subaru's U.S. vehicle sales rose 33
percent, and Volvo posted a 4 percent increase. Saab's sales fell
26 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
