<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Agricultural Sector in Kazakhstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank okayed here
Tuesday a 15 million U.S. dollar loan for the agricultural post
privatization assistance project in Kazakhstan to support its
newly privatized farms and agro-enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The loan is the first in a series of adjustable program loans
for the agricultural sector. More flexible than traditional sector
investments, these loans make up a sequence of small loans to
support phased implementation of long-term development programs.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project, including physical and price
contingencies, is some 23.78 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Since Kazakhstan joined the World Bank in 1992, the bank has
committed a total of 1.35 billion dollars for 15 projects.
</P>
