<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Poverty-Reduction Project in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Tuesday a 225 million U.S. dollar loan for poverty reduction and
rural development project in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The kecamatan development project is designed to increase
economic opportunities and raise rural incomes, strengthen
kecamatan (subdistrict) and village government and community
institutions, and build public infrastructure through labor
intensive methods.
</P>
<P>
The project's decentralized and community-based design limits
the need for direct government intervention. Technical assistance
for engineering and community facilitation is provided by private
sector companies and non-governmental organizations.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is estimated at 273 million
dollars. Apart from the World Bank loan, the Indonesian government
will contribute 47 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
